- Pi pico PIO(assembly code for the pico, storing registers) is the next thing we r going to talk about(you can go pretty quick, 250 mHz, can be very noisy and slip a bit at higher frequencies)
- what we're using RF signals for
- fast/iota 30.5 mHz: rf frequency of the beam in this machine
- BPM's are given a reference signal that are basically the structure of the beam
- in booster where you are ramping(36-53), the main injector also ramps but it's 55.6xxx - 536xx(at what point does the board break down...percision of it)
